<br>
This game used to be fun. I am beginning to think it isn't anymore.<br>
<br>
My guild is growing up now, and grown up guilds get to do what?<br>
<br>
Argue with other grown up guilds about camps and spawns and loots...<br>
<br>
Arrrrggghhh it does my head in completely.... but there is no solution to basic human selfishness, don't slate Giggy for stating what is probably true..<br>
<br>
Why don't raid calendars work? Because someone will use them to determine a time they can turn up before the raid and farm away..<br>
<br>
I don't think there are any solutions, to give Verant credit they have tried.<br>
<br>
e.g. The Warrens for newbies, and the changes to Vox/Naggy for people over 52, but the latter doesn't work (except with nodrop loot) because most level 60s have at least 1 46-52 alternate which they can use to raid em..<br>
<br>
I hope they keep trying until they find a solution that actually works... for a start moving that item on Vox for the Pally epic on to some non level specific mob would be sensible...<br>
<br>
Some interesting possibilities for solutions would be '1 character' servers... ie no ALTS, this would remove the farming for twinks problems.. (though the lack of mules for bank space would be a major pain)<br>
<br>
Introduce a new loot type called USABLEDROP that is completely unlootable by anyone other than a class/race designed to use it.. <br>
<br>
More item level restrictions (a la Primal Velium) to discourage farming...<br>
<br>
Make it impossible for higher levels to zone into certain zones.. (making sure no serious quests impacted)<br>
<br>
Verant enforced raid calendars<br>
<br>
Verant also need to do so something to encourage higher level players to play for fun, not just cash..<br>
<br>
i.e. fun quests a la PoM that don't involve time based camps, but randomised puzzles. <br>
<br>
Level expansion beyond level 60 available based on accepting some new terms and conditions designed to prevent exploitation of powers... (ie to stop level 80 necros from soloing Planes... make mobs in old zones immune to level 60+ players and vice versa - the exception being trade skill dropping mobs)<br>
<br>
I don't know if any of these would work, but there must be some way to resurrect the game, besides even with all the camp stealing, KSing, Ninjalooting, swearing and demands for clarity/sow/ports/buffs/cash/items  - i'll prolly still play because my guild are cool to chat too, and the graphics are nicer than ICQ <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Good luck with your fear/hate raid, I'd come but my guild has plans to go someplace else that night, and taking Giggy's advice - I ain't saying where ;P<br>
<br>
Herrick<br>
<br>
